    narr:narration """This hub collects the verbatim record — direct quotes and attributed observations — that anchor the aswritten narrative from early 2025 through mid-2026. The earliest witness is [the customer's CTO's friends-and-family quip](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOFriendsAndFamilyQuote) (Jul 2025), followed by the March 2026 [modular-synthesizer reaction](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletModularSynthesizerQuote) and [\"This is incredible\"](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletIncredibleQuote) moment — the product demonstrating itself through its own output. April 2026 surfaces the buyer-side thesis: [the customer's CTO naming perspective over information and code](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOInformationCommodity), [the customer's CTO on AI slop](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOAISlopQuote), and [the customer's chief architect's unprompted goal-directed riff](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerArchitectGoalRiffQuote) alongside [the customer's chief architect's skepticism baseline](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerArchitectSkepticismQuote). May 2026 adds the curated-memory cluster: [the customer's CTO's PR-with-unit-tests metaphor](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOPRMetaphorQuote), [Scarlet's human-review requirement](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletCantAutomateQuote), [the customer's chief architect's discomfort with unreviewed dumps](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerArchitectNotComfortableQuote), and [Scarlet's Sunday-scaries self-assessment](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletSundayScaries) framing the base-camp moment. July 2026 closes with [Scarlet's cutover authorization](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_CutoverBlockquoteEvidence) and [the [amount] bridge statement](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_CorrectionVerbatimQuote). The corpus is structured around direct block-quoted speech as primary evidence, with [verbatim attribution as the governing style](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_DirectQuoteStyle).""" ;
